

* Practice to upgrade containerD

#    Practice upgrade k8s versions  - https://v1-22.docs.kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/administer-cluster/kubeadm/kubeadm-upgrade/

    # Update the repositiry
        sudo apt update

    #Check the latest versions of kubeadm
        sudo apt-cache madison kubeadm
#Upgrade kubeadm
    #unhold kubeadm
    sudo apt-mark unhold kubeadm

    # Check for the lastest kubernetes release versions
    sudo apt update &&  sudo apt install -y kubeadm=1.22.x-00 && \
    sudo apt-mark hold kubeadm

    #Note: kubeadm upgrade also automatically renews the certificates that it manages on this node. To opt-out of certificate renewal the flag --certificate-renewal=false can be used. For more information see the certificate management guide - https://v1-22.docs.kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/administer-cluster/kubeadm/kubeadm-certs/

    sudo kubeadm upgrade plan
    sudo kubeadm upgrade apply vx.xx.xx
    
